2. Zero-Shot and Few-Shot Prompting

The zero-shot and few-shot results have been analysed in detail in the preceding section. We briefly summarise the key findings here for completeness within the full results narrative. Qwen2.5-7B zero-shot achieves macro-averaged entity F1 of 0.518 and establishes the strongest prompting baseline. Few-shot prompting (k = 1, full dialogues) degrades F1 to 0.499 for Qwen and from 0.432 to 0.385 for Mistral, with hallucination rates increasing by 3.4 and 4.6 percentage points respectively. Safety scores remain below 3.0/5.0 under both prompting conditions for both models. Zero-shot Qwen2.5-7B is adopted as the primary prompting reference point against which translation and fine-tuning results are compared.
 
